headline: Treasury Yields Rise on Upbeat Jobs Signal
summary: Treasury yields climbed following a reassuring signal from the JOLTS report that the labor market hasn’t deflated too much since the summer.

headline: ‘Fodder for a recession’: Top economist Mark Zandi warns about so many Americans ‘already living on the financial edge’ in a K-shaped economy
summary: The latest JOLTS report shows hiring stuck at 3.2% and quits falling again as the Fed prepares to cut rates.

headline: Job openings inched up in October, but labor market worries persist
summary: Job openings ticked slightly higher in October, surpassing economists’ expectations, government data released Tuesday showed.

headline: ADP Announces 2026 HCM Distinction Award Finalists
summary: ADP, a global leader in HR and payroll solutions, today announced the finalists for the 2026 HCM Distinction Awards. Celebrating the transformation of work, the awards program recognizes a select group of large employers that demonstrate excellence in HCM and lead the way in workplace innovation.

headline: ADP National Employment Report Preliminary Estimate for November 22, 2025
summary: For the four weeks ending November 22, 2025, U.S. private employers added an average of 4,750 jobs per week, according to the NER Pulse, a weekly update of the monthly ADP National Employment Report (NER).

headline: 1 Large-Cap Stock on Our Buy List and 2 We Turn Down
summary: Large-cap stocks have the power to shape entire industries thanks to their size and widespread influence. With such vast footprints, however, finding new areas for growth is much harder than for smaller, more agile players.
